00204 target_ulong next_task_struct(target_ulong addr)
00205 {
00206   target_ulong retval;
00207 
00208   if (0xC031E000 == taskaddr)
00209     // this is for kernel 2.4.20
00210     TEMU_read_mem(addr + listoffset, sizeof(retval), &retval);
00211   else {
00212     // default is kernel 2.6
00213     target_ulong next;
00214 
00215     TEMU_read_mem(addr + listoffset + sizeof(target_ulong), 
00216       sizeof(target_ulong), &next);
00217     retval = next - listoffset;
00218   }
00219 
00220   return retval;
00221 }

00232 target_ulong get_pgd(target_ulong addr)
00233 {
00234   target_ulong mmaddr, pgd;
00235   TEMU_read_mem(addr + mmoffset, sizeof(mmaddr), &mmaddr);
00236   if (0 == mmaddr)
00237     TEMU_read_mem(addr + mmoffset + sizeof(mmaddr), 
00238     sizeof(mmaddr), &mmaddr);
00239 
00240   if (0 != mmaddr)
00241     TEMU_read_mem(mmaddr + pgdoffset, sizeof(pgd), &pgd);
00242   else
00243     memset(&pgd, 0, sizeof(pgd));
00244 
00245   return pgd;
00246 }

00291 void get_mod_name(target_ulong addr, char *name, int size)
00292 {
00293   target_ulong vmfile, dentry;
00294   if (TEMU_memory_rw(addr + vmfileoffset, &vmfile, sizeof(vmfile), 0) == -1
00295       || TEMU_memory_rw(vmfile + dentryoffset, &dentry, sizeof(dentry),
00296                         0) == -1
00297       || TEMU_memory_rw(dentry + dinameoffset, name, size < 36 ? size : 36,
00298                         0) == -1)
00299     name[0] = 0;
00300 }

00302 int init_kernel_offsets()
00303 {
00304   int i = 0;
00305   int retval = -1;
00306   char buf[128];
00307 
00308   while (strlen(kernel_table[i].version) != 0) {
00309 
00310     hookingpoint = kernel_table[i].hookingpoint;
00311     hookingpoint2 = kernel_table[i].hookingpoint2;
00312     taskaddr = kernel_table[i].taskaddr;
00313     tasksize = kernel_table[i].tasksize;
00314     listoffset = kernel_table[i].listoffset;
00315     pidoffset = kernel_table[i].pidoffset;
00316     mmoffset = kernel_table[i].mmoffset;
00317     pgdoffset = kernel_table[i].pgdoffset;
00318     commoffset = kernel_table[i].commoffset;
00319     commsize = kernel_table[i].commsize;
00320     vmstartoffset = kernel_table[i].vmstartoffset;
00321     vmendoffset = kernel_table[i].vmendoffset;
00322     vmnextoffset = kernel_table[i].vmnextoffset;
00323     vmfileoffset = kernel_table[i].vmfileoffset;
00324     dentryoffset = kernel_table[i].dentryoffset;
00325     dnameoffset = kernel_table[i].dnameoffset;
00326     dinameoffset = kernel_table[i].dinameoffset;
00327 
00328     //term_printf("trying %d: %s\n", i, kernel_table[i].version); 
00329     TEMU_memory_rw(taskaddr + commoffset, buf, 128, 0);
00330     if (strcmp(buf, "swapper") == 0) {
00331       retval = i;
00332       kernel_mem_start = 0xC0000000;
00333       break;
00334     }
00335 
00336     i++;
00337   }
00338 
00339   return retval;
00340 }

00342 static uint32_t hook_handles[sizeof(kernel_table)/sizeof(struct koffset)];
00343 
00344 void for_all_hookpoints(hook_proc_t func, int action)
00345 {
00346   int i = 0;
00347 
00348   while (strlen(kernel_table[i].version) != 0) {
00349     if (action) 
00350       hook_handles[i] = hookapi_hook_function(1, kernel_table[i].hookingpoint,
00351                             func, NULL, 0);
00352     else
00353       hookapi_remove_hook(hook_handles[i]);
00354 
00355     i++;
00356   }
00357 
00358   return;
00359 }
